text: Dobrić () is a village in Serbia. It is situated in the Šabac municipality, in the Mačva District. The village has a Serb ethnic majority and its population numbering 1,205 people (2002 census). The Church of Saints Peter and Paul stands in the town. ==See also== *List of places in Serbia *Mačva Category:Mačva Category:Populated places in Mačva District
